<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12093b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12093b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12093b"> 93(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> M carries her umbrella</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">S&apos;il ne lui pla&icirc;t pas, elle doit lui accorder au moins un tour pendant lequel elle lui fait comprendre qu&apos;il perd ses frais, ou bien, elle s&apos;arrange pour le quitter. D&egrave;s que la jeune fille a consenti, le galant prend son parapluie et le lui porte; il ne lui donne le bras que s&apos;il la conna&icirc;t beaucoup. <br><font color="green">[If she does not like him, she has to give him at least one round during which she makes him understand that she is not interested, or she gets ready to leave him. As soon as the young girl agrees, <mark>the young gallant carries her umbrella</mark> and brings it to her; he does not take her arm unless he knows her very well.]</font> <small> Paul-Yves S&eacute;billot, <a name="RDTP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RDTP"><cite title="source">Traditions et coutumes de Basse Bretagne</cite></a> (1904) 349-50</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
